<paragraph id="5E3936DBFFA7FFA5FF0C81B5007DA61C" blockId="1.[151,1437,500,2037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Color and pilosity. Body covered by short, brown pubescence and semi-recumbent golden setae. Head dorsally and ventrally dark brown. Eyes red. Antennae and legs shining yellow, except tibiae and tarsi brown. Rostrum shining brown except for segment IV dark black; genital segments shining brown. Pronotum with anterior transverse yellow band. Venter of abdomen dark grey; abdominal sternite VII centrally with black pubescence.</paragraph>
